name: Pondok Bali Raden Kawan Home Stay
address: J52P+P9F, Tua, Marga, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1:
Very hospitable family with 4 guest rooms surrounded by rice and flower fields. The location is strategically located to explore the nearby waterfalls and rice terraces as well as driving up into the mountains.

The rooms are big and clean flaunting a big comfortable bed with proper linen sheets. Toilet and shower are en suite.
There is also a kitchen travelers can use to cook themselves if desired, though we did not make use of it.

We arrived here after dark without notice looking for room and they went out of their way to accommodate us. We even got invited to join a ceremony the family was hosting the following day to honor a recently deceased member, which was very special.

We can whole heartedly recommend this home stay!
review 2: Very nice house at the edge of the rice fields. Wayan and her family welcomed us as if we were part of their family, always concerned about our comfort and infinite kindness. We keep a very good memory of our stay and images of so many smiles in the head. Thanks to Wayan and his family for the wonderful moments of exchange
review 3: We had a very nice stay with the Kawan family! Lovely people, great accomodation, scenic, neat and clean house in the rice fields and awsome impressions from the balinese culture!
